The paper deals with optimization problems related to vehicle routing and tourist trip design, which are typically studied in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO). The use of stochastic travel times and risk-sensitive criteria suggests a focus on data science (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. Finally, the development of a local search algorithm indicates a possible connection to optimization and control theory (cs.SI).
